      • stage

        public Software.StageInvocation stage(java.lang.String cluster,
                                      SoftwareTypes.StageSpec spec)
        Description copied from interface: Software
        Stages the desired software document associated with the given cluster to hosts within the cluster. If getCommit() property is Set, it implies the minimum commit that the Software.stage(java.lang.String, com.vmware.esx.settings.clusters.SoftwareTypes.StageSpec) method should use, however if subsequent commits have been made to the desired state document the stage method will use the most recent desired state document. The result of this operation can be queried by calling the cis/tasks/{task-id} where the task-id is the response of this operation. This method was added in vSphere API 8.0.0.1.

        Invocation Result:
        The result of the Software.stage(java.lang.String, com.vmware.esx.settings.clusters.SoftwareTypes.StageSpec) method.

        Operation Errors:
        Error - If there is an unknown internal error. The accompanying error message will give more details about the failure.
        InvalidArgument - If the getCommit() property of spec specifies an invalid commit, or the getHosts() property of spec specifies an invalid host or a host not part of the cluster, or the cluster is not managed with a single software specification.
        NotAllowedInCurrentState - If there is another operation in progress.
        NotFound - If there is no cluster associated with cluster in the system or if desired software document is not found.
        ServiceUnavailable - If the service is not available.
        TimedOut - If the operation times out.
        Unauthenticated - If the caller is not authenticated.

        Specified by:
        stage in interface Software
        Parameters:
        cluster - Identifier of the cluster. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: ClusterComputeResource.
        spec - stage specification.
        Returns:
        instance of Software.StageInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described stage operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.

      • check

        public Software.CheckInvocation check(java.lang.String cluster,
                                      SoftwareTypes.CheckSpec spec)
        Description copied from interface: Software
        Runs checks on the cluster before applying the desired software document across all hosts in the cluster. Checks if all hosts in the cluster are in a good state to be updated with the desired software document. If getCommit() property is Set it implies the minimum commit that the check method should use, however if subsequent commits have been made to the desired state document the check method will use the most recent desired state document. The result of this operation can be queried by calling the cis/tasks/{task-id} where the task-id is the response of this operation.

        Invocation Result:
        The results of all checks performed.

        Operation Errors:
        Error - If there is unknown internal error. The accompanying error message will give more details about the failure.
        InvalidArgument - If the getCommit() property of spec specifies an invalid commit, or the getHosts() property of spec specifies an invalid host or a host not part of the cluster.
        NotAllowedInCurrentState - If there is another operation in progress or if the getCommit() property of spec specifies a commit that has already been applied.
        NotFound - If there is no cluster associated with cluster in the system.
        ServiceUnavailable - If the service is not available.
        TimedOut - If the operation times out.
        Unauthenticated - If the caller is not authenticated.

        Specified by:
        check in interface Software
        Parameters:
        cluster - Identifier of the cluster. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: ClusterComputeResource.
        spec - Check specification.
        Returns:
        instance of Software.CheckInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described check operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
